International Jazz Day took place on Sunday and this year, Safaricom celebrated the day with a Kenyan Edition Safaricom Jazz concert at the Carnivore Grounds.The concert, titled Kenyan Jazz All Stars Edition, was headlined by a stellar line-up of Kenyan jazz musicians.These included Nairobi Horns Project, Shamsi Music, Mwai &amp; The Truth, AfroSync, Edward Parseen and The Different Faces, Jacob Asiyo &amp; Kavutha Mwanzia-Asiyo, James Gogo, Juma Tutu, Eddie Grey and Chris Bittok.Also in the line-up were Ghetto Classics, who are quickly making a name for themselves as some of Kenya&rsquo;s most musically gifted youngsters.